{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "9f3c1b50-7e8a-4d9b-9c70-1b8a4f2c0a01",
    "name": "GetAvails Backend API",
    "description": "Authentication API for the GetAvails / ArtistBook backend.\n\n## Quick start\n\n1. Set the `base_url` collection variable (default: `http://localhost:8000`).\n2. Run **Auth — Registration → Register** with a fresh email.\n3. Copy the 6-digit OTP printed in the Django server console (dev uses the console email backend) into the `verification_otp` collection variable.\n4. Run **Auth — Registration → Verify Email** — this auto-saves `access_token`, `refresh_token`, and `user_email` to the collection.\n5. All subsequent requests pick up the stored tokens automatically.\n\n## Auto-saved variables\n\n| Variable | Set by |\n|---|---|\n| `access_token` | Login, Verify Email, Google Sign In, Refresh Token |\n| `refresh_token` | Login, Verify Email, Google Sign In, Refresh Token |\n| `reset_token` | Password Reset Verify |\n| `user_email` | Register, Login, Verify Email, Google Sign In |\n\n## Error response shape\n\nEvery error follows:\n```\n{\n  \"success\": false,\n  \"error\": {\n    \"code\": \"<stable-string>\",\n    \"status\": <http-status>,\n    \"message\": \"<human readable>\",\n    \"details\": { ... }\n  }\n}\n```\nFrontend should switch on `error.code`. Notable codes: `email_not_verified` (login before OTP), `account_not_found` (Google sign-in for unknown identity), `authentication_failed`, `invalid`, `throttled`.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "base_url", "value": "http://localhost:8000", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "access_token", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "refresh_token", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "reset_token", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "user_email", "value": "jane@example.com", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "verification_otp", "value": "000000", "type": "string", "description": "Paste the 6-digit OTP shown in the Django console (dev) or sent by email (prod) before running Verify Email or Password Reset Verify." },
    { "key": "artist_user_id", "value": "", "type": "string", "description": "User ID of an artist (the User PK, not ArtistProfile PK) — used for booking offer creation and public artist availability." },
    { "key": "artist_profile_id", "value": "", "type": "string", "description": "ArtistProfile PK — used for catalog detail and favorites." },
    { "key": "venue_id", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "conversation_id", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "offer_id", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "availability_date", "value": "2026-06-15", "type": "string" }
  ],
  "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Auth — Registration",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Register",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 201 Created', () => pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.equal(201));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('success flag', () => pm.expect(body.success).to.be.true);",
                  "if (body.email) pm.collectionVariables.set('user_email', body.email);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/register/",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "register", ""]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Jane Doe\",\n  \"email\": \"{{user_email}}\",\n  \"password\": \"S3cure!Pass\",\n  \"role\": \"artist\"\n}"
            },
            "description": "Create a new account.\n\n**Body:** `name`, `email`, `password`, `role` (one of `artist`, `agent`, `talent_buyer`, `venue`, `organizer`).\n\n**Response 201:** `{ success, message, email }`. Account is created with `email_verified_at = null` and a 6-digit OTP is emailed. The user cannot log in until the OTP is verified."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Verify Email (OTP)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.equal(200));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (body.access) pm.collectionVariables.set('access_token', body.access);",
                  "if (body.refresh) pm.collectionVariables.set('refresh_token', body.refresh);",
                  "if (body.user && body.user.email) pm.collectionVariables.set('user_email', body.user.email);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/register/verify/",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "register", "verify", ""]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"{{user_email}}\",\n  \"otp\": \"{{verification_otp}}\"\n}"
            },
            "description": "Verify the email-verification OTP. On success the account is marked verified and JWT tokens are issued — this is when the frontend should navigate to **\"You're all set!\"**.\n\n**Set `verification_otp`** in the collection variables before running this (read it from the Django runserver console in dev).\n\n**Response 200:** `{ success, message, user, access, refresh }`. Tokens are saved automatically by the test script."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Resend Verification OTP",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/register/resend/",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "register", "resend", ""]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"{{user_email}}\"\n}"
            },
            "description": "Resend the verification OTP to an unverified account.\n\n**Response 200** (always, even if the account doesn't exist or is already verified — does not leak account state).\n\nA 60-second resend cooldown is enforced server-side; calling too quickly returns a `Throttled` error."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Auth — Login",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Login (Email + Password)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.equal(200));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (body.access) pm.collectionVariables.set('access_token', body.access);",
                  "if (body.refresh) pm.collectionVariables.set('refresh_token', body.refresh);",
                  "if (body.user && body.user.email) pm.collectionVariables.set('user_email', body.user.email);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/login/",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "login", ""]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"{{user_email}}\",\n  \"password\": \"S3cure!Pass\",\n  \"remember_me\": true\n}"
            },
            "description": "Email + password login.\n\n`remember_me=true` extends refresh-token TTL to `JWT_REMEMBER_ME_REFRESH_TTL_DAYS` (default 30 days) instead of the default 1 day.\n\n**Response 200:** `{ success, user, access, refresh }`.\n\n**403 with `error.code = email_not_verified`** if the account hasn't completed OTP verification — frontend should route to the Verification Code screen."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Google Sign In",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200 or 404', () => pm.expect([200, 404]).to.include(pm.response.code));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (body.success) {",
                  "  if (body.access) pm.collectionVariables.set('access_token', body.access);",
                  "  if (body.refresh) pm.collectionVariables.set('refresh_token', body.refresh);",
                  "  if (body.user && body.user.email) pm.collectionVariables.set('user_email', body.user.email);",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/google/",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "google", ""]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"id_token\": \"<paste-google-id-token-here>\"\n}"
            },
            "description": "Sign in with a Google ID token (SPA pattern — frontend obtains the token from Google's library and posts it here).\n\nNew Google identities are **rejected** with `404 account_not_found`; the frontend should redirect to Sign Up. Existing email accounts get their `google_sub` auto-linked on first successful Google login.\n\n**Response 200:** `{ success, user, access, refresh }`."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Auth — Tokens & Profile",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Refresh Token",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.equal(200));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (body.access) pm.collectionVariables.set('access_token', body.access);",
                  "if (body.refresh) pm.collectionVariables.set('refresh_token', body.refresh);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/refresh/",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "refresh", ""]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"refresh\": \"{{refresh_token}}\"\n}"
            },
            "description": "Exchange a valid refresh token for a new access (and refresh) token. Refresh-token rotation is enabled, so the old refresh is blacklisted on success."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Logout",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{access_token}}", "type": "string" }]
            },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/logout/",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "logout", ""]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"refresh\": \"{{refresh_token}}\"\n}"
            },
            "description": "Blacklist the refresh token so it can't be reused. Returns **205 Reset Content** on success."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Current User",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{access_token}}", "type": "string" }]
            },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/me/",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "me", ""]
            },
            "description": "Return the currently authenticated user's profile.\n\n**Response 200:** `{ success, user: { id, email, name, role, image, email_verified_at, is_staff, created_at } }`."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Auth — Password Reset",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Request Reset",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/password-reset/request/",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "password-reset", "request", ""]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"{{user_email}}\"\n}"
            },
            "description": "Step 1 — send a 6-digit reset OTP to the provided email.\n\nReturns **200** unconditionally (never reveals whether the email is registered). 60-second resend cooldown applies."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Verify OTP",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.equal(200));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (body.reset_token) pm.collectionVariables.set('reset_token', body.reset_token);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/password-reset/verify/",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "password-reset", "verify", ""]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"{{user_email}}\",\n  \"otp\": \"{{verification_otp}}\"\n}"
            },
            "description": "Step 2 — verify the OTP. On success returns a short-lived (10 min), single-use, signed `reset_token` that authorizes the next step.\n\nThe test script saves `reset_token` to the collection automatically.\n\n**Set `verification_otp`** in collection variables before running this."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Confirm Reset",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/password-reset/confirm/",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "password-reset", "confirm", ""]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"reset_token\": \"{{reset_token}}\",\n  \"new_password\": \"NewS3cure!Pass\",\n  \"confirm_password\": \"NewS3cure!Pass\"\n}"
            },
            "description": "Step 3 — set the new password.\n\nOn success, **all outstanding refresh tokens for the user are blacklisted** (forces re-login on every device). The reset token is also invalidated by the password change (its fingerprint is tied to the old password hash)."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Profile",
      "item": [
